# ─── Build-time · GitHub stats ───────────────────────────────
# Fine-grained PAT, read-only on Metadata + Contents.
# Used to fetch live repo stats at build for /dev and the home /github banner.
# Without it, build still works but uses anonymous limits + cached fallback.
# Create at: https://github.com/settings/personal-access-tokens/new
# Vercel: Settings → Environment Variables → GITHUB_TOKEN
GITHUB_TOKEN=github_pat_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ─── Edge runtime · /api/chat (Claude console) ───────────────
# Anthropic API key for the live console on the home page.
# Without it the console falls back to mock replies — still works in dev.
# Create at: https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
# Vercel: Settings → Environment Variables → ANTHROPIC_API_KEY (Production + Preview)
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-api03-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ─── Client · Microsoft Clarity (heatmaps + session replay) ──
# 10-char project ID. If unset, Clarity loader is a no-op (site works fine).
# Create at: https://clarity.microsoft.com (free, no cap on session count).
# PUBLIC_ prefix exposes the value to the browser bundle (intended — Clarity
# is a public tag).
# Vercel: Settings → Environment Variables → PUBLIC_CLARITY_ID (Production + Preview)
PUBLIC_CLARITY_ID=xxxxxxxxxx

# ─── Client · Google Maps (wanderings travel map) ────────────
# Maps JS API key, HTTP-referrer-restricted in Google Cloud Console (safe to
# expose). Without it the travel map falls back to a static placeholder.
# Create at: https://console.cloud.google.com/google/maps-apis/credentials
# Vercel: Settings → Environment Variables → PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY
PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=AIzaSyXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

# ─── Runtime · /api/chat rate limit (Upstash / Vercel KV) ────
# Persistent per-IP daily limit for the chat endpoint. Without these the limiter
# silently falls back to per-instance in-memory counting (no real daily cap).
# Provision via Vercel Marketplace (Upstash Redis); it injects either the KV_*
# or UPSTASH_* pair. Set whichever your integration provides.
# Vercel: Settings → Environment Variables (Production + Preview)
KV_REST_API_URL=https://xxxxxxxx.upstash.io
KV_REST_API_TOKEN=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=https://xxxxxxxx.upstash.io
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
